HEADWORD: Narcotine
<hw>Nar"co*tine</hw> <pr>(n⟦aum⟧r"k⟦osl⟧*t⟦icr⟧n <it>or</it>
n⟦aum⟧r"k⟦osl⟧*t⟦emac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>narcotine</ets>. Cf. <er>Cotarnine</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An alkaloid found in opium, and extracted as a white crystalline
substance, tasteless and less poisonous than morphine; -- called also
<altname>narcotia</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Narcotinic</ent>⟦br⟧
